Head ( Fig. 6G ). Dorsal sclerites as Fig. 5A . SI as Fig. 6H . Head 210–300, 250 μm long, cephalic index 0.73– 0.88, 0.83. Lengths of first to fifth antennal segments (in µm) ( Fig. 5B ): 40–50, 47; 8.3–12.5, 10.7; 4.8–5, 4.9; 6.6–8, 7.6; 3.2–5.2; 4.2; AR 1.1–2.0, 1.5. Basal segments 3.3–4.8, 3.8 times as long as basal width. Blade 23–35, 38 μm long; Bl/Fl 0.8–1.0, 0.92. Premandible ( Fig. 5C ) 42–60, 53 μm long. Mandible ( Fig. 5D ) 50–60 µm long.. Mentum 50–73, 63 µm wide, with 4 median and 6 pairs of lateral teeth ( Fig. 5E ). Ventromental plate 50–82, 70 µm wide (
Fig. 6I
). Distance between setae submenti 100–120, 106 µm long. Postmentum 167–230, 206 µm long.

Distribution . This species has been recorded from Sakhalin Island in Russia ( Tokunaga 1940 ); Hokkaido Island, Kii Penisula, Seto Inland Sea, Yakushima Island and Okinawa Islands in Japan ( Sasa 1988 ; Sasa & Suzuki 2000 ;
Kawai et al . 2011
, 2015 ;
Yamamoto et al . 2015
); Gangwon-do in South Korea ( Ree 2013 ). We could add the records from Guangdong and Zhejiang in China and South Jeolla ( Jeollanam-do ) in Sourth Korea ( Fig. 1 ).
